               <p>Fourth Middlesex Jury, before Mr. Sergeant 
               <persName id="t18310908-310-person2239">Arabin</persName>
            .</p>
               <p>1837. 
               <persName id="t18310908-310-defend2240" type="defendantName">
                  MARY 
                  CROSS
               <interp inst="t18310908-310-defend2240" type="surname" value="CROSS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-defend2240" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-defend2240" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-defend2240" type="age" value="28"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18310908-310-off1592" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-off1592" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-off1592" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18310908-310-cd1593" type="crimeDate">26th of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-310-off1592 t18310908-310-cd1593"></join>, 1 sovereign, the monies of 
                     <persName id="t18310908-310-victim2241" type="victimName">
                        John 
                        Hood
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-victim2241" type="surname" value="Hood"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18310908-310-victim2241" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18310908-310-victim2241" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-310-off1592 t18310908-310-victim2241"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JOHN HOOD. I am a <rs id="t18310908-310-viclabel1594" type="occupation">seaman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-310-victim2241 t18310908-310-viclabel1594"></join>; I came home in the Cambridge. I put into the hands of my landlady three sovereigns and a half, on the 24th of August; next day I went there, and called for a glass of liquor, asked for the money, and gave them the card they had given me; they gave me the three sovereigns; I said, "Change the halfsovereign, and take for the liquor;" the prisoner came in, put her hand into my hand, and took out a sovereign - I turned round, and said, "Give me that sovereign;" she put her hand to her mouth, and said, "I have not your sovereign, I have not seen it;" she said she wanted a pint of beer - the landlady took her backwards, and overhauled her; but the sovereign has never been found - I had never spoken to her before; I do not know that I had seen her.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-310-person2242">
                  MARY 
                  ELIZABETH PERKINS
               <interp inst="t18310908-310-person2242" type="surname" value="ELIZABETH PERKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-person2242" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-person2242" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My father keeps the <placeName id="t18310908-310-crimeloc1595">White-hart public-house, Shadwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-310-crimeloc1595" type="placeName" value="White-hart public-house, Shadwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-310-crimeloc1595" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-310-off1592 t18310908-310-crimeloc1595"></join>. The prosecutor left three sovereigns and a half with us; he came and had the three sovereigns, and wanted change for the halfsovereign; I saw the prisoner take a sovereign out of his hand - he mentioned it directly, and she was searched, but it has never been found.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-310-person2243">
                  JOHN 
                  MITCHELL
               <interp inst="t18310908-310-person2243" type="surname" value="MITCHELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-person2243" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-person2243" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-officer. I took the prisoner, but found nothing on her.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went to get a pint of beer; there were several young women there, and one of them, whom I knew, asked me to have a glass of liquor, which I did; I was coming out, and the prosecutor said I had taken his sovereign - I had never seen it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310908-310-verdict1596" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-verdict1596" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 28. - <rs id="t18310908-310-punish1597" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-310-punish1597" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-310-defend2240 t18310908-310-punish1597"></join>
               Transported for Fourteen Years
            </rs>.</p>
